Customer Support Chatbot Documentation
Overview
This project implements a customer support chatbot designed to handle common queries, track orders, and escalate unresolved issues to human agents. It demonstrates real-world use cases such as:

Knowledge base lookups

Order tracking via simulated API

Password reset assistance

Intelligent escalation to human agents

Conversation memory and issue classification

Features
Knowledge Base: Provides instant answers to FAQs (e.g., return policy, shipping, payment).

Order Tracking: Retrieves order status using order ID or customer email.

Password Reset: Initiates password reset flow with email verification.

Issue Classification: Automatically categorizes queries into types (billing, technical, general, etc.).

Escalation: Connects customers to human agents after repeated unresolved queries.

Conversation Memory: Stores dialogue history for context-aware responses.

Architecture
1. IssueType Enum
Defines categories of support requests:

ORDER_TRACKING

PASSWORD_RESET

RETURN_POLICY

BILLING

TECHNICAL

GENERAL

2. OrderStatus Enum
Represents simulated order states:

PENDING, SHIPPED, IN_TRANSIT, DELIVERED, CANCELLED

3. KnowledgeBase Class
Stores FAQs with regex-based matching.

Provides quick answers to common queries.

4. OrderDatabase Class
Simulates customer orders.

Supports lookup by order ID or email.

5. CustomerSupportChatbot Class
Core chatbot logic:

Preprocesses input

Classifies issues

Routes queries to appropriate handlers

Escalates unresolved issues

Maintains conversation memory

Key Methods
Method	Description
preprocess	Normalizes user input text.
classify_issue	Determines issue type using regex.
extract_order_id	Extracts order ID from text.
extract_email	Extracts email address from text.
handle_order_tracking	Provides order status details.
handle_password_reset	Initiates password reset flow.
respond	Main response logic with routing and escalation.
_escalate_to_human	Connects customer to human agent.
chat	Interactive chat loop for CLI use.

Type exit or quit to leave.

Run in Single Query Mode:-
python3 chatbot.py "Where is my order ORD-001?"
Processes a single query and returns a response.

